# INBXIFY Tech Debt Tracker

**Purpose.** Single source of truth for known-but-accepted shortcuts across the INBXIFY codebase. Every item here is deliberate (not a bug) but will cost us later if unaddressed. Grep this file before touching a module — the answer to "why is it like this?" is usually here.

**Last updated:** April 20, 2026
**Session anchor:** Studio Phase 2 Session 1 complete

---

## How to read this doc

Each item has:
- **Unique ID** — `TD-NNN` (tech debt), `HC-NNN` (hardcoded value), `RN-NNN` (rename/migration)
- **Status** — Active / Blocked / Resolved / Accepted-Forever
- **Priority** — H (blocks multi-tenant or causing bugs) / M (fix before Publisher #2) / L (nice-to-have)
- **Location** — exact file + function/line if applicable
- **Fix trigger** — the condition that makes this worth paying down

Priority isn't urgency. Priority is *blast radius if we don't fix it.*

