## ACTIVE — STUDIO / TA STUDIO

### 🔵 TD-101 — Scenario F `getArticleBody` route does not exist
**Priority:** H
**Location:** Make.com Scenario F; exposed by `uploads-processor-v1.0.8.js:190` (`fetchArticleBody`)
**Symptom:** Studio body editor button calls `window.InbxEditBody`, which GETs `?action=getArticleBody` against `TA_CONFIG.makeAssembly`. Make.com responds with the literal string `"Accepted"` (Make's default response for webhooks without a Response module) instead of JSON. `fetchArticleBody` chokes parsing: `SyntaxError: Unexpected token 'A', "Accepted" is not valid JSON`. InbxRTE never opens.
**Blast radius:** Body editing non-functional in Studio. All other Studio fields (27 of 28 smoke test steps) work.
**Fix trigger:** Session 2 Part A — first item.
**Fix spec:** Add a `getArticleBody` route to Scenario F. Route reads the Webflow Article item, returns `{ body: "<html>", content: "", html: "" }` JSON shape that `fetchArticleBody` expects.
**Notes:** Discovered during Studio v1.1.1 smoke test, April 19 evening. Previously undiscovered because no UI actually called `InbxEditBody` before Studio.

### 🟢 TD-102 — Studio save endpoint is stubbed (console.log only)
**Priority:** H
**Location:** `ta-studio-v1.1.1.js` → `triggerSave()` (line ~431)
**Symptom:** Save button generates a complete payload but does not POST to Scenario F. Payload logs to console; fake 700ms success flash simulates a round-trip. Dirty flags clear but Webflow CMS is unchanged.
**Blast radius:** Zero data writes from Studio. Editors see apparent success but nothing persists. **Session 1 ships this way deliberately** — the stub is the safe default until Scenario F's `updateArticleFields` route exists.
**Fix trigger:** Session 2 Part A — after `getArticleBody` works.
**Fix spec:** Replace `console.log(...)` with `fetch(CFG.makeAssembly, { method: 'POST', body: JSON.stringify(payload) })`. Add error handling; clear the success flash only after a 200 response.

### 🔵 TD-103 — Option field translation strategy unresolved
**Priority:** H (per Session 2 prereq)
**Location:** `ta-studio-v1.1.1.js` → `triggerSave()` payload construction; affects `articleStatus`, `revenueType`, any other option-bound fields in future collections
**Symptom:** Webflow option fields (e.g. `article-status`, `Revenue Type`) bind to their **display label** not their ID hash. Confirmed empirically April 19: DOM shows `"Draft"` / `"Live"` as `data-article-status` values. Studio payload carries those labels through to Scenario F. Webflow API likely needs the hash.
**Blast radius:** Every option-field write may fail until we pick a translation point.
**Fix trigger:** Session 2 — the moment we build Scenario F's HTTP/Webflow update module. The module's configuration will reveal whether we need to translate.
**Three candidate fixes:**
  - **(a)** Accept labels at Scenario F, translate label→hash inside Make.com via a mapper module
  - **(b)** Translate in Studio using `TA_CONFIG.optionIds` (already seeded for articleStatus, revenueType, reListingStatus)
  - **(c)** Discover Webflow API actually accepts labels — no translation needed
**Notes:** `window.TA_CONFIG.optionIds` was added April 19 as forward-compatible config. If we choose (a) or (c), the optionIds block becomes dead code and can be removed.

### ⚫ TD-104 — `window.InbxEditBody` lives in `uploads-processor-v1.0.8.js` but no UI there calls it
**Priority:** L
**Location:** `uploads-processor-v1.0.8.js:768-809`
**Symptom:** `editArticleBody()` is defined and registered to `window.InbxEditBody`, but the Uploads Processor has no button that invokes it. It was declared speculatively for future modules. Studio is now the first caller.
**Blast radius:** None — it works where it sits. But architectural drift: Studio depends on Uploads Processor being loaded on the T-A page for RTE launching.
**Proposed home:** `ta-rte-v1.0.0.js` itself (register there so loading the RTE also registers its public launcher), or a dedicated `ta-studio-rte-bridge.js`.
**Accepted-forever UNLESS:** Uploads Processor ever gets retired before Studio is re-pointed. Then the function disappears with it. Low risk while both modules coexist on the T-A page, but flag this if the load order or script list ever changes.

### 🟢 RN-101 — Studio file rename complete; old files remain as archive
